# Account-Admin credentials for Azure.
#
# SECURITY: This file contains secrets.  It is gitignored.  Never commit it.
#
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 1 — Databricks credentials (REQUIRED)
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# DATABRICKS_ACCOUNT_ID
#   Your Databricks account UUID.  The Service Principal must have
#   the Databricks Account Admin role.
#   https://accounts.azuredatabricks.net  > top-right menu > "Account ID"
#
# DATABRICKS_CLIENT_ID / DATABRICKS_CLIENT_SECRET
#   Account Console > User Management > Service Principals > <your SP>
#   > "Application ID"  →  CLIENT_ID
#   > "OAuth Secrets"  > Generate Secret  →  CLIENT_SECRET

DATABRICKS_ACCOUNT_ID       =
DATABRICKS_CLIENT_ID        =
DATABRICKS_CLIENT_SECRET    =

# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 2 — Azure settings
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID
#   Azure Portal > Subscriptions > Subscription ID
#
# AZURE_RESOURCE_GROUP
#   Resource group for test resources (storage accounts, access connectors).
#   Must already exist.
#   Azure Portal > Resource Groups > <your RG> > name
#
# AZURE_REGION
#   Must match the region of your Azure Databricks workspace.
#   Examples: eastus2, westus2, australiaeast, westeurope
#
# AZURE_TENANT_ID
#   Azure Portal > Microsoft Entra ID > Overview > "Tenant ID"
#
# AZURE_CLIENT_ID / AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET
#   An Azure AD App Registration (Service Principal).
#   Azure Portal > Microsoft Entra ID > App registrations > <your app>
#   > "Application (client) ID"  →  AZURE_CLIENT_ID
#   > Certificates & secrets > New client secret  →  AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET
#
#   ⚠  Azure client secrets expire (default 6 months / 2 years).
#      If teardown fails with an auth error, generate a new secret and re-run.
#
# Required RBAC roles on the resource group
#   The Service Principal needs these roles on AZURE_RESOURCE_GROUP.
#   An account with role-assignment permission must run:
#
#     az role assignment create \
#       --assignee <AZURE_CLIENT_ID> \
#       --role "Contributor" \
#       --scope "/subscriptions/<AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID>/resourceGroups/<AZURE_RESOURCE_GROUP>"
#
#     az role assignment create \
#       --assignee <AZURE_CLIENT_ID> \
#       --role "Storage Blob Data Contributor" \
#       --scope "/subscriptions/<AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID>/resourceGroups/<AZURE_RESOURCE_GROUP>"
#
#   Role                          Why
#   ───────────────────────────   ─────────────────────────────────────────────
#   Contributor                   Create/delete storage accounts, access connectors
#   Storage Blob Data Contributor Manage blob data in ADLS Gen2 containers
#
#   Optional — if the SP also has User Access Administrator, it can assign
#   managed-identity roles itself.  If not, the script falls back to your
#   local Azure CLI login (az login) for role assignments.  This is common
#   in enterprise environments with ABAC-constrained Owner roles.
#
# Auto-created resources
#   The provision script creates an ADLS Gen2 storage account
#   (genietest<run-id>), a container, and a Databricks Access Connector
#   with a managed identity.  All resources are deleted on teardown.

AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID       =
AZURE_RESOURCE_GROUP        =
AZURE_REGION                = eastus2
AZURE_TENANT_ID             =
AZURE_CLIENT_ID             =
AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET         =
